From f552d74e815e19d04bb8ebd3be1cf715d4bf67a4 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Andre Mauricio Zelak <andre.zelak@windriver.com>
Date: Mon, 1 Jun 2026 17:49:36 -0300
Subject: [PATCH 09/11] Fix HA enable/disable lock and forced lock commands

This commit fixes the HA commands:
* forced lock <interface>
* enable lock <interface>
* disable lock <interface>

Correct an indexing error in starts_with where the final character
of the prefix was skipped. This resolves an issue where the function
incorrectly accepted misspelled keywords.

Correct the string comparisson in ha_handle_enable_lock_msg,
ha_handle_enable_source_msg and ha_handle_disable_source_msg functions.
This resolves an issue where those functions failed to find the domain
corresponding to the interface name.

Correct the src_name variable validation in ha_handle_enable_lock_msg,
ha_handle_enable_source_msg and ha_handle_disable_source_msg functions.
Fix an issue when the interface name is not provided as argument.

Check src_domain and prev_src_domain pointers before derreferencing them
in reconfigure function.

Initilize now variable at resource allocation in do_loop and reconfigure
functions. This resolve possible access before initialization when
clock_gettime function fails.

Reduce to debug level the entry messages in match requirements check
functions.

Test Plan:
PASS Deploy an SX system with T-GM configuration, HA enabled and
     two ptp4l instances.

     When 'enable lock <interface>' is requested
     Then phc2sys disables the automatic clock source selection algorithm
     And selects as source the domains represented by the interface

     When 'status' command is requested
     Then the result points the selected source is the interface of the
     previous command.
     And the 'Source forced?' is 'yes'.

     When 'disable lock' command is requested
     Then phc2ys re-enables the automatic clock source selection algorithm
     And runs the algoritm

     When 'disable source <interface>' is called passing the currect selected
     interface
     Then the interface is removed from the list of available interfaces
     And phc2sys run the algorithm to select a new source

     When 'disable source <interface>' is called passing the last available
     interface name
     Then the command is rejected
     And the error message "Error: Last interface enabled" is returned

PASS (Negative case) 'enable loc' command is rejected, and the error message
     "Error: Invalid command" is returned.

PASS (Negative case) the commands 'enable lock', 'enable source' and
     'disable source' not followed by an interface name are rejected, and
     the following error message with usage example is returned.

PASS (Negative case) the commands 'enable lock', 'enable source' and
     'disable source' followed by an invalid interface name are rejected,
     and the following error message is returned.
     "Error: Interface not found"

Signed-off-by: Andre Mauricio Zelak <andre.zelak@windriver.com>
